<section xml:id="rational-functions">
    <title>Rational Functions</title>
    <definition xml:id="rational-function">
  <title>Definition</title>
  <statement><p>A function <m>r(x)</m> is <term>rational</term> if there exist two polynomial functions <m>p(x)</m> and <m>q(x)</m> such that
    <me>r(x) = \frac{p(x)}{q(x)}</me>
  </p></statement>
</definition>

<example xml:id="determine-rational-or-not-1">
  <title>Determine if a Function is Rational or Not</title>
  <statement>
    <p>Determine if the following functions are rational or not.</p>
    <p>
      <ol>
        <li><p><m>f(x) = \frac{3x - 4}{x^2 - x + 3}</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>f(x) = \frac{3}{x^2 - 1}</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>f(x) = x^2 + x + 1</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>f(x) = \frac{x^2 - 2\sqrt{x} + 1}{x^4 + 1}</m></p></li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
<p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>
                This is a rational function since both the numerator and denominator are polynomials.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Since constants such as <m>3</m> are polynomials, this is a rational function.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                Since we can rewrite this polynomial as <m>\frac{x^2 + x + 1}{1}</m> and <m>1</m> is a polynomial, this is a rational function.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                The numerator is not a polynomial because there is a variable under the radical symbol. This is not a rational function.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
</p>
  </solution>
</example>
</section>